    <h3>Document Credit System</h3>
    <p>Each plan has an annual document allowance that determines how many documents can be created or optimized per year. Discovery: 120 documents. Standard and Pro: 360 documents. Peace of Mind: unlimited (fair usage policy applies). Surfer's documentation defines a "document" as any content creation or optimization action — editing an existing document appears to count the same as creating a new one. The exact boundaries of what counts as a document were not fully clarified from the available documentation.</p>

    <h3>Pricing Analysis</h3>
    <p>At €99/month (Standard), Surfer offers solid value for small teams: Content Editor, Surfer AI, plagiarism checker, and ChatGPT visibility tracking. However, the jump to Pro (€182/month) is substantial — €83 more per month for daily AI prompt refresh across all models, internal linking suggestions, cannibalization reports, Contentful integration, and 5 brand workspaces. For most serious SEO teams, Pro is the minimum viable tier, bringing the effective cost to approximately €2,184/year. Compared to Semrush at $129/month or Ahrefs at $129/month, Surfer is competitively priced for an all-in-one content optimization platform — but those tools include broader marketing capabilities (backlinks, advertising, social media) that Surfer does not offer.</p>

    <Callout type="info">
      <strong>Research note:</strong> Surfer's pricing page emphasizes annual billing. Monthly prices are approximately 17-20% higher per month. The plan names changed in early 2026 — previous tiers (Essential, Advance, Max) were replaced with Discovery, Standard, Pro, Peace of Mind, and Enterprise.
