  <section id="design">
    <h2>Platform &amp; Build Quality</h2>
    <p>Surfer is a browser-based SaaS platform accessible through any modern web browser. The content editor operates entirely online and provides real-time SEO optimization guidelines as the user writes. The platform also offers browser extensions (Chrome), integrations with WordPress, Google Docs, and Contentful, and a full API for custom workflows.</p>

    <h3>Technology Architecture</h3>
    <p>Surfer's core technology is based on NLP (Natural Language Processing) and machine learning models that analyze over 500 signals from top-ranking pages for any given keyword. When a user opens the Content Editor for a target keyword, Surfer: (1) fetches current SERP data for that keyword; (2) analyzes the top-ranking pages for signals including word count, keyword density, NLP term usage, headings structure, readability, image optimization, and more; (3) generates a Content Score based on how well the current draft matches the ranking signals; (4) provides real-time, specific recommendations for improvement — add a section about this topic, increase keyword density here, restructure headings, and so on. The algorithms are trained on what actually ranks in Google and updated continuously.</p>

    <h3>AI Model Architecture</h3>
    <p>Surfer AI uses a proprietary generation engine specifically trained for SEO-optimized content. Unlike general-purpose AI writing tools like ChatGPT or Jasper, Surfer AI incorporates the Content Editor's optimization guidelines directly into the generation process — meaning the AI produces content that is pre-optimized based on current SERP signals rather than requiring a separate optimization pass. The AI Tracker module queries live AI models (ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews, Google AI Mode, Gemini) using configurable prompts to check how a brand is mentioned, and returns visibility scores and mention gap analysis.</p>

    <h3>Security &amp; Compliance</h3>
    <p>Surfer is ISO 27001 certified and GDPR-compliant. All infrastructure is hosted in Europe, emphasizing "100% made and hosted in Europe" as a sovereignty advantage. The platform offers SSO/SAML on Enterprise plans. Data is encrypted at rest and in transit. The platform's European hosting is a meaningful differentiator for organizations with data residency requirements.</p>

    <h3>Visual Appeal &amp; Trust Signals</h3>
    <p>The Surfer website presents a modern, clean interface with a dark sidebar nav. Trust signals on the public site include a customer count of 150,000+, logo walls featuring major brands (Allianz, ClickUp, FedEx, Shopify, Bolt, DHL, Intuit, L'Oréal), review ratings of 4.8/5 on G2 and 4.9/5 on Capterra, 200+ case studies, and ISO 27001 certification. The Positive Group parent company branding is prominent throughout.</p>
  </section>

