  <section id="history">
    <h2>Company Background</h2>
    <p>Surfer was originally founded as SurferSEO in approximately 2017. The company was later acquired by Positive Group, a European tech holding company based in Wrocław, Poland. Positive Group also owns Positive User (CRM and marketing automation — formerly User.com) and Positive Signitic (email signature management). Surfer operates as "Positive Surfer" within the group while maintaining its product identity at surferseo.com.</p>

    <h3>Market Position &amp; Growth</h3>
    <p>Surfer claims 150,000+ customers and 800,000+ users across 159+ countries, with 45,000 paying customers. Enterprise customers include Allianz, Bolt, ClickUp, FedEx, Shopify, Hostinger, and Intuit. The platform has a 4.8/5 rating on G2 (500+ reviews), 4.9/5 on Capterra (400+ reviews), and 4.6/5 on Trustpilot (200+ reviews). Positive Group operates as a "European digital sovereignty" company with local hosting infrastructure.</p>

    <h3>Product Evolution</h3>
    <p>Surfer's product development trajectory shows clear evolution: originally a content optimization tool (Content Score), then expanded to AI content generation (Surfer AI), then content strategy (Topical Map, Content Audit), and most recently AI visibility monitoring (AI Tracker). The 2026 rebrand to "Positive Surfer" and integration with the Positive Group ecosystem signals an ambition to offer a broader marketing platform, though the CRM and automation products remain separate.</p>

    <h3>Affiliate Program</h3>
    <p>Surfer operates an affiliate program through https://surferseo.com/affiliate-program/. Specific commission rates, cookie durations, and program terms were not captured in this research. Verification is needed before including an affiliate link in the CTA.</p>
